relies on but does not ship.

JA4 / JA4+ (FoxIO LLC)
----------------------
- The JA4 TLS fingerprinting algorithm is licensed under BSD-3. See
  https://github.com/FoxIO-LLC/ja4 for the upstream specification.
- JA4+ fingerprints (JA4S/JA4H/JA4X and related variants) are licensed
  under the FoxIO License 1.1, which restricts commercial use.
  BeaconButty's use of JA4+ in this repo is for non-commercial /
  internal-use deployment only. Commercial users must obtain an OEM
  licence from FoxIO (john@foxio.io).

See docs/development/licensing.md for the full analysis.

Suricata rules
--------------
Any Suricata rules loaded on top of config/local.rules (typically the
Emerging Threats Open ruleset) are subject to their own licence terms.
BeaconButty does not redistribute those rules.

